The following submission has been created.

Track Name: Computer Engineering=20

Paper ID: 117

Paper Title: Social Media Analytics for Trend Prediction Using Machine Lear=
ning

Abstract:
With the surge in popularity of social media platforms, a new, large-time d=
ata source created by users has emerged, such as posts, hashtags, comments =
and shares, which are all indicative of real-time opinions and trends that =
capture the zeitgeist of the public. Trend analysis is a task tackled by ma=
ny existing tools which is usually done through occasional surveys and the =
data typically gathered from the past. Trend analysis has not been agile en=
ough to maintain pace with the real-time discussion taking place on social =
media. In the present work, a comprehensive machine learning (ML) framework=
 is proposed to predict trends on social media based on Natural Language Pr=
ocessing (NLP) for pre-processing different types of classifiers. We extrac=
t a multi-dimensional feature space from the text based on TF-IDF vectorisa=
tion and hashtag frequency and engagement. Three supervised classifiers =E2=
=80=93 Logistic Regression, Naive Bayes, Random Forest =E2=80=93 are traine=
d, evaluated and compared. Results of our experiments indicate that, the Ra=
ndom Forest has the highest accuracy in predicting the trend (91%) among th=
e rest other models in all the metrics. Time-series visualisations that con=
firm the capability of the system to predict a trend onset by 4.2 hours ahe=
ad as well.

